#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure a Network Team Using the Command Line"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Network Team Using teamd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a network team, a JSON format configuration file is required for "
"the virtual interface that will serve as the interface to the team of ports "
"or links. A quick way is to copy the example configuration files and then "
"edit them using an editor running with <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> privileges. To list the available example configurations, enter "
"the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>ls /usr/share/doc/teamd-*/example_configs/</command>\n"
"activebackup_arp_ping_1.conf  activebackup_multi_lw_1.conf   loadbalance_2."
"conf\n"
"activebackup_arp_ping_2.conf  activebackup_nsna_ping_1.conf  loadbalance_3."
"conf\n"
"activebackup_ethtool_1.conf   broadcast.conf                 random.conf\n"
"activebackup_ethtool_2.conf   lacp_1.conf                    roundrobin_2."
"conf\n"
"activebackup_ethtool_3.conf   loadbalance_1.conf             roundrobin.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To view one of the included files, such as <filename>activebackup_ethtool_1."
"conf</filename>, enter the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>cat /usr/share/doc/teamd-*/example_configs/"
"activebackup_ethtool_1.conf</command>\n"
"{\n"
"	\"device\":	\"team0\",\n"
"	\"runner\":	{\"name\": \"activebackup\"},\n"
"	\"link_watch\":	{\"name\": \"ethtool\"},\n"
"	\"ports\":	{\n"
"		\"eth1\": {\n"
"			\"prio\": -10,\n"
"			\"sticky\": true\n"
"		},\n"
"		\"eth2\": {\n"
"			\"prio\": 100\n"
"		}\n"
"	}\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a working configurations directory to store <systemitem class="
"\"daemon\">teamd</systemitem> configuration files. For example, as normal "
"user, enter a command with the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>mkdir ~/<replaceable>teamd_working_configs</replaceable></"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy the file you have chosen to your working directory and edit it as "
"necessary. As an example, you could use a command with the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>cp /usr/share/doc/teamd-*/example_configs/"
"activebackup_ethtool_1.conf \\ ~/<replaceable>teamd_working_configs</"
"replaceable>/activebackup_ethtool_1.conf</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To edit the file to suit your environment, for example to change the "
"interfaces to be used as ports for the network team, open the file for "
"editing as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>vi ~/<replaceable>teamd_working_configs</replaceable>/"
"activebackup_ethtool_1.conf</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make any necessary changes and save the file. See the <filename>vi(1)</"
"filename> man page for help on using the <application>vi</application> "
"editor or use your preferred editor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that it is essential that the interfaces to be used as ports within the "
"team must not be active, that is to say, they must be <quote>down</quote>, "
"when adding them into a team device. To check their status, issue the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>ip link show</command>\n"
"1: lo: &lt;LOOPBACK,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 65536 qdisc noqueue state UNKNOWN "
"mode DEFAULT\n"
"    link/loopback 00:00:00:00:00:00 brd 00:00:00:00:00:00\n"
"2: em1: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast "
"state UP mode DEFAULT qlen 1000\n"
"    link/ether 52:54:00:d5:f7:d4 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n"
"3: em2: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast "
"state UP mode DEFAULT qlen 1000\n"
"  link/ether 52:54:00:d8:04:70 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example we see that both the interfaces we plan to use are "
"<quote>UP</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To take down an interface, issue a command as <systemitem class="
"\"username\">root</systemitem> in the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>ip link set down em1</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Repeat for each interface as necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a team interface based on the configuration file, as <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, change to the working "
"configurations directory (<replaceable>teamd_working_configs</replaceable> "
"in this example):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]#&nbsp;<command>cd /home/<replaceable>user</"
"replaceable><replaceable>teamd_working_configs</replaceable></command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Then issue a command in the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]#&nbsp;<command>teamd -g -f activebackup_ethtool_1.conf -d</command>\n"
"Using team device \"team0\".\n"
"Using PID file \"/var/run/teamd/team0.pid\"\n"
"Using config file \"/home/<replaceable>user</replaceable>/"
"teamd_working_configs/activebackup_ethtool_1.conf\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>-g</option> option is for debug messages, <option>-f</option> "
"option is to specify the configuration file to load, and the <option>-d</"
"option> option is to make the process run as a daemon after startup. See the "
"<filename>teamd(8)</filename> man page for other options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To check the status of the team, issue the following command as <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]#&nbsp;<command>teamdctl team0 state</command>\n"
"setup:\n"
"  runner: activebackup\n"
"ports:\n"
"  em1\n"
"    link watches:\n"
"      link summary: up\n"
"      instance[link_watch_0]:\n"
"        name: ethtool\n"
"        link: up\n"
"  em2\n"
"    link watches:\n"
"      link summary: up\n"
"      instance[link_watch_0]:\n"
"        name: ethtool\n"
"        link: up\n"
"runner:\n"
"  active port: em1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To apply an address to the network team interface, <interface>team0</"
"interface>, issue a command as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> in the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>ip addr add 192.168.23.2/24 dev team0</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To check the IP address of a team interface, issue a command as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"~]$&nbsp;<command>ip addr show team0</command>\n"
"4: team0:  &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue "
"state UP \n"
"    link/ether 16:38:57:60:20:6f brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n"
"    inet 192.168.23.2/24 scope global team0\n"
"       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever\n"
"    inet6 2620:52:0:221d:1438:57ff:fe60:206f/64 scope global dynamic \n"
"       valid_lft 2591880sec preferred_lft 604680sec\n"
"    inet6 fe80::1438:57ff:fe60:206f/64 scope link \n"
"       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To activate the team interface, or to bring it <quote>up</quote>, issue a "
"command as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> in the following "
"format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>ip link set dev team0 up</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To temporarily deactivate the team interface, or to take it <quote>down</"
"quote>, issue a command as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> "
"in the following format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>ip link set dev team0 down</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To terminate, or kill, an instance of the team daemon, as <systemitem class="
"\"username\">root</systemitem> user, issue a command in the following format:"
""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>teamd -t team0 -k</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>-k</option> option is to specify that the instance of the daemon "
"associated with the device <interface>team0</interface> is to be killed. See "
"the <filename>teamd(8)</filename> man page for other options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For help on command-line options for <systemitem class=\"daemon\">teamd</"
"systemitem>, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]$&nbsp;<command>teamd -h</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "In addition, see the <filename>teamd(8)</filename> man page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Network Team Using ifcfg Files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a networking team using <literal>ifcfg</literal> files, create a "
"file in the <filename class=\"directory\">/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/</"
"filename> directory as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=team0\n"
"DEVICETYPE=Team\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"BOOTPROTO=none\n"
"IPADDR=192.168.11.1\n"
"PREFIX=24\n"
"TEAM_CONFIG='{\"runner\": {\"name\": \"activebackup\"}, \"link_watch\": "
"{\"name\": \"ethtool\"}}'"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This creates the interface to the team, in other words, this is the master."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a port to be a member of <interface>team0</interface>, create one "
"or more files in the <filename class=\"directory\">/etc/sysconfig/network-"
"scripts/</filename> directory as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DEVICE=eth1\n"
"HWADDR=D4:85:64:01:46:9E\n"
"DEVICETYPE=TeamPort\n"
"ONBOOT=yes\n"
"TEAM_MASTER=team0\n"
"TEAM_PORT_CONFIG='{\"prio\": 100}'"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add additional port interfaces similar to the above as required, changing "
"the DEVICE and HWADDR field to match the ports (the network devices) being "
"added. If port priority is not specified by <literal>prio</literal> it "
"defaults to <literal>0</literal>; it accepts negative and positive values in "
"the range <literal>-32,767</literal> to <literal>+32,767</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifying the hardware or MAC address using the <command>HWADDR</command> "
"directive will influence the device naming procedure. This is explained in "
"<xref linkend=\"ch-Consistent_Network_Device_Naming\" />."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To bring up the network team, issue the following command as <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]#&nbsp;<command>ifup team0</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To view the network team, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid "~]$&nbsp;<command>ip link show</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add a Port to a Network Team Using iputils"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
