#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure the loadbalance Runner"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This runner can be used for two types of load balancing, active and passive. "
"In active mode, constant re-balancing of traffic is done by using statistics "
"of recent traffic to share out traffic as evenly as possible. In static "
"mode, streams of traffic are distributed randomly across the available links."
" This has a speed advantage due to lower processing overhead. In high volume "
"traffic applications this is often preferred as traffic usually consists of "
"multiple stream which will be distributed randomly between the available "
"links, in his way load sharing is accomplished without intervention by "
"<systemitem class=\"daemon\">teamd</systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To configure the loadbalance runner for passive transmit (Tx) load "
"balancing, using an editor as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>, add the following to the team JSON format configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"{\n"
" \"device\": \"team0\",\n"
" \"runner\": {\n"
"   \"name\": \"loadbalance\",\n"
"   \"tx_hash\": [\"eth\", \"ipv4\", \"ipv6\"]\n"
" },\n"
" \"ports\": {\"em1\": {}, \"em2\": {}}\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration for hash-based passive transmit (Tx) load balancing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To configure the loadbalance runner for active transmit (Tx) load balancing, "
"using an editor as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, add the "
"following to the team JSON format configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"{\n"
"   \"device\": \"team0\",\n"
"   \"runner\": {\n"
"     \"name\": \"loadbalance\",\n"
"     \"tx_hash\": [\"eth\", \"ipv4\", \"ipv6\"],\n"
"     \"tx_balancer\": {\n"
"       \"name\": \"basic\"\n"
"     }\n"
"   },\n"
"   \"ports\": {\"em1\": {}, \"em2\": {}}\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configuration for active transmit (Tx) load balancing using basic load "
"balancer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure the LACP (802.3ad) Runner"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To configure the LACP runner using <application>ethtool</application> as a "
"link watcher, using an editor as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>, add the following to the team JSON format configuration file:"
